Educational Purpose

Cancer Metabolism Explorer is an educational visualization of cancer
metabolism and tumor bioenergetics. It is intended to summarize and illustrate
concepts from the published scientific literature to support learning and
discussion. It is not a validated computational model of tumor metabolism and
must not be used to estimate tumor biology, predict treatment response, or
guide clinical decision-making.

Medical Disclaimer

This software is an educational resource. It does not recommend treatments and
must not be used for decisions regarding cancer diagnosis, prevention, or
therapy. Treatment decisions should always be made in consultation with
qualified healthcare professionals using evidence-based clinical guidelines.

Model Scope

The pathway values displayed throughout the application are conceptual
illustrations of relative metabolic tendencies. They are not percentages,
measured biological quantities, patient-specific values, or validated
predictions. Guided cancer profiles represent literature-informed educational
syntheses of metabolic patterns commonly described for those tumor types and
are not intended to represent any individual patient's tumor.

Scientific Scope and Limitations

The project synthesizes mechanisms reported across published cancer metabolism
research. While efforts have been made to accurately represent the cited
literature, scientific understanding continues to evolve, and the application
is not exhaustive. Inclusion of a pathway, mechanism, publication, or
experimental agent should not be interpreted as establishing scientific
consensus, clinical efficacy, or endorsement by the cited authors.

Evidence Interpretation

The application discusses interventions supported by varying levels of
evidence, ranging from approved medications with extensive human pharmacology
to investigational therapies and preclinical research. Mechanistic plausibility
does not establish clinical benefit. Many investigational or off-patent
compounds have not undergone large randomized oncology trials, and clinical
efficacy remains unestablished unless demonstrated through appropriate human
studies.

No Warranty of Scientific Accuracy

Although substantial effort has been made to accurately summarize published
research, no warranty is made regarding scientific completeness, future
accuracy, or suitability for any particular purpose. Users are encouraged to
consult the original cited literature and relevant evidence-based clinical
guidelines when interpreting scientific concepts presented by this project.